Description: The data in this sheet is used in generating the SECIM report. It is identical to data included in the other sheets, but positive and negative ionization mode data are combined and redundant results have been removed. Data in this sheet can be linked to the complete lists of analyzed peaks in other sheets by the "row.mode" column.
The unique row identifier and ionization mode of the row. This field can be used to link a result to the complete (un-reduced) results in other sheets.
Compound name as identified by SECIM internal database or HMDB (via R package metid). If peak could not be identified by either method, the peak's mz_RT is used.
Left side contrast - Right side contrast
Confidence level of ID (1 for peaks identified with SECIM database, 3 if HMDB via metid.)
metid: total score (same as mz match score when RT is not used for matching)
Fold-Change (processed data) Left side/ Right side
Low-confidence tag for peaks with a "3" level identification
The processed but un-normalized peak intensity data
